Intervention: Contrast-enhanced spectral mammography for the detection breast cancer .
Full field digital mammography for the detection breast cancer
Eligibility: Heterogeneously or extremely dense breasts (BI-RADS category c or d).
Pregnant or lactating as determined by routine standard practice
History of prior breast excisional biopsy (Patients with a history of core needle biopsy will not be excluded)
History of prior breast reduction mammoplasty surgery
History of prior breast augmentation surgery
Mental condition rendering the subject unable to understand the nature, scope, and possible consequences of the study.
Results: The primary endpoint of this study is to determine the accuracy of DE CE mammography when compared to full field digital mammography (FFDM) in patients with increased breast density (Breast Imaging-Reporting And Data System (BI-RADS) category c or d breast density).
Arm/Group Description: Contrast-enhanced spectral mammography for the detection breast cancer .
Unit of Measure: percentage of accuracy  100        (29 to 100)
Arm/Group Description: Full field digital mammography for the detection breast cancer
Unit of Measure: percentage of accuracy  67        (9 to 99)
